{"title":"---","markdown":{"headingText":"---","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n```\nARCHITECTURE.md\n```\n\n---\n\n# ARCHITECTURE.md\n\nCVX — Distributed HPC Vision AI Platform\n\n---\n\n# 1. Overview\n\nCVX is a distributed, high-performance Vision AI platform designed for:\n\n* Petabyte-scale storage\n* Terabyte-scale memory\n* Multi-node GPU clusters (H100-class hardware)\n* Streaming and batch processing\n* Agentic multimodal reasoning\n* Distributed training and serving\n\nThe system is modular, memory-aware, storage-agnostic, and designed for\nlarge-scale production deployments.\n\n---\n\n# 2. High-Level Architecture\n\n## 2.1 Layered Logical Architecture (Mermaid)\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TB\n    A[Application Layer]\n    B[Agentic Reasoning Layer]\n    C[Model Serving Layer]\n    D[Distributed Compute Layer]\n    E[Streaming + Batch Layer]\n    F[Memory + Cache Layer]\n    G[Storage Abstraction Layer]\n\n    A --> B\n    B --> C\n    C --> D\n    D --> E\n    E --> F\n    F --> G\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2.2 Logical Stack (SVG)\n\n```{=html}\n<svg width=\"600\" height=\"400\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"20\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e6f2ff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"45\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Application Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"70\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#d9edf7\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"95\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Agentic Reasoning Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"120\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#cce5ff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"145\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Model Serving Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"170\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#b3daff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"195\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Distributed Compute Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"220\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#99ccff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"245\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Streaming + Batch Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"270\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#80bfff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"295\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Memory + Cache Layer</text>\n\n<rect x=\"50\" y=\"320\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#66b3ff\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n<text x=\"300\" y=\"345\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Storage Abstraction Layer</text>\n</svg>\n```\n\n---\n\n# 3. Repository Structure\n\n```\ncvx/\n├── docker/\n├── k8s/\n├── benchmarks/\n├── tests/\n├── pyproject.toml\n└── cvx/\n    ├── core/\n    ├── memory/\n    ├── cache/\n    ├── storage/\n    ├── models/\n    ├── image/\n    ├── video/\n    ├── multimodal/\n    ├── agent/\n    ├── features/\n    ├── search/\n    ├── anomaly/\n    ├── streaming/\n    ├── distributed/\n    ├── serving/\n    ├── edge/\n    ├── training/\n    ├── experiments/\n    ├── reporting/\n    └── api/\n```\n\nThe outer `cvx/` is the repository root.\nThe inner `cvx/` is the Python package.\n\n---\n\n# 4. Memory and Cache Architecture\n\n## 4.1 Data Flow (Mermaid)\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TD\n    A[Object Storage]\n    B[NVMe Cache]\n    C[Memory-Mapped Dataset]\n    D[Ray Object Store]\n    E[Pinned CPU Memory]\n    F[GPU HBM Memory]\n    G[CUDA Streams]\n\n    A --> B\n    B --> C\n    C --> D\n    D --> E\n    E --> F\n    F --> G\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4.2 Memory Hierarchy (SVG)\n\n```{=html}\n<svg width=\"600\" height=\"300\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"20\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f2f2f2\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"45\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Object Storage (PB)</text>\n\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"70\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e6e6e6\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"95\" text-anchor=\"middle\">NVMe Cache</text>\n\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"120\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#d9d9d9\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"145\" text-anchor=\"middle\">RAM (Memory-Mapped)</text>\n\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"170\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"195\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Pinned CPU Memory</text>\n\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"220\" width=\"500\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#bfbfbf\" stroke=\"#000\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"245\" text-anchor=\"middle\">GPU HBM (H100)</text>\n</svg>\n```\n\n---\n\n# 5. Distributed Compute Architecture\n\n## 5.1 Ray + Spark Integration (Mermaid)\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart LR\n    A[Kafka]\n    B[Ray Cluster]\n    C[Spark Cluster]\n    D[GPU Workers]\n    E[Model Serving]\n\n    A --> B\n    B --> D\n    C --> B\n    D --> E\n```\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n* Ray: training, serving, GPU scheduling\n* Spark: feature engineering, ETL\n* Kafka: streaming ingestion\n\n---\n\n# 6. Multi-GPU Serving\n\n## 6.1 Serving Flow (Mermaid)\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart LR\n    A[Client Request]\n    B[Load Balancer]\n    C[Dynamic Batching]\n    D[CUDA Graph Execution]\n    E[Multi-GPU Inference]\n    F[Response]\n\n    A --> B --> C --> D --> E --> F\n```\n\nCapabilities:\n\n* CUDA Graph capture\n* Tensor parallel execution\n* FP8/BF16 precision\n* NVLink topology awareness\n\n---\n\n# 7. Agentic Vision Architecture\n\n## 7.1 Agent Reasoning Loop (Mermaid)\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TD\n    A[Input]\n    B[Perception]\n    C[Memory Graph]\n    D[Tool Router]\n    E[Reasoning Loop]\n    F[Action Execution]\n\n    A --> B\n    B --> C\n    C --> D\n    D --> E\n    E --> F\n```\n\nCapabilities:\n\n* Scene understanding\n* Retrieval-augmented reasoning\n* Multi-step decision making\n* Tool orchestration\n\n---\n\n# 8. Streaming Architecture\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart LR\n    A[Kafka Producer]\n    B[Kafka Broker]\n    C[Microbatch Processor]\n    D[Inference Pipeline]\n    E[Feature Store]\n\n    A --> B --> C --> D --> E\n```\n\nSupports:\n\n* Backpressure handling\n* Event-driven inference\n* Streaming feature updates\n\n---\n\n# 9. Storage Abstraction\n\nAll storage backends implement a common interface:\n\n* Local filesystem\n* S3-compatible storage\n* GCS\n* Azure Blob\n* OpenSearch\n* Feature stores\n\nThis ensures portability across cloud and on-prem deployments.\n\n---\n\n# 10. Testing Strategy\n\n```\ntests/\n├── unit/\n├── integration/\n├── distributed/\n├── memory/\n└── performance/\n```\n\nTesting domains:\n\n* API validation\n* Distributed coordination\n* Memory stability\n* GPU throughput\n* Streaming latency\n\n---\n\n# 11. Deployment Topologies\n\n## 11.1 Development\n\n* Single-node\n* Docker Compose\n* Mock storage\n\n## 11.2 Staging\n\n* Small Ray cluster\n* Kafka single broker\n* Multi-GPU node\n\n## 11.3 Production\n\n* Multi-node Ray cluster\n* Kafka cluster\n* Spark cluster\n* Distributed object storage\n* H100 GPU nodes\n\n---\n\n# 12. Scalability Model\n\n| Dimension | Capability                 |\n| --------- | -------------------------- |\n| Storage   | Petabyte-scale             |\n| Memory    | TB RAM + GPU HBM           |\n| Compute   | Horizontal Ray scaling     |\n| Serving   | Multi-GPU dynamic batching |\n| Streaming | Kafka-based real-time      |\n| Training  | Distributed multi-node     |\n\n---\n\n# 13. Design Guarantees\n\n* Modular layer isolation\n* Memory-aware data flow\n* Storage abstraction\n* Distributed-first architecture\n* GPU-optimized execution\n* Agentic multimodal extensibility\n\n---\n\n# 14. Summary\n\nCVX is designed as a distributed AI platform capable of handling:\n\n* Large-scale storage\n* High-throughput GPU inference\n* Continuous training\n* Real-time streaming\n* Agentic multimodal reasoning\n\nThe architecture ensures extensibility, scalability, and hardware efficiency\nacross cloud, on-prem, and edge environments.\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":true,"echo":false,"output":true,"warning":false,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,